name: Highway K'tchen, Dabolim - Dine In & Take-Away

reviews.review_text: The place have a good vibe there. I have ordered Deluxe non veg thali and paw bhaji. Both have a great taste and I recommend you to buy and taste them.

After a long drive from Bangalore to Goa, too tired to explore eateries in the area due to rain, we found a good one near hotel that we stayed. The Highway Kitchen authentic punjabi restaurant in Vasco da gama is the best pick. Visited this place for little snacks but ended up having dinner. We initially tried Belgium hot chocolates that tasted good.
Later ordered for Panner manchurian which was absolutely dipped in the sauces and the chilly flavour enhanced the dish.
Ordered chole batura, the authentic punjabi style and filling. Chole batura served with mint chutney, pickle and onions. One of the best chole batura we have tried.
To end the meal, we ordered one vanilla cream milkshake and one sweet lassi. Both were top notch, the vanilla cream milkshake is their top sellers.
The service was fast and good. The servers were friendly and helped us with the choices of food. The ambience gives you a feel of dhaba which is family friendly.
Overall, you want to experience an authentic punjabi dhaba style, a must visit place.

Courteous staff, good recommendations, good food too. The miasi the roti and butter chicken is a killer combination, combined with sweet lassi! The thali is a good option for lunch. The jalebis we ordered were made fresh and simply melted in my mouth.
